wikipedia_page.main: Sir Arthur Selborne Jelf, CMG (10 October 1876 – 26 February 1947) was a British colonial administrator. He should not be confused with his relative, the English judge Sir Arthur Richard Jelf.

response: # in 1876 Katherine Frances, younger daughter of Charles Browne Dalton, vicar of St. Michael's, Highgate, who survived him; by her he had three sons and four daughters. Their son Sir Arthur Selborne Jelf was a colonial administrator.
